Question Text: You have been tasked to find out whether the Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) is enabled globally. Which command will you type?
Choices:
a. show protocols
b. show cdp
c. show running-config
d. show interface brief
LLM Explanation: The 'show running-config' command is used to display the current configuration of the router, including whether CDP is enabled globally. CDP is usually enabled by default on Cisco devices, and this command will show all the current settings that are actively configured on the device, including CDP settings.
